metadata.name: 𝓐𝓹𝓹𝓻𝓸𝓿𝓪𝓵
metadata.description: And above all, watch with glittering eyes, for the stars are young, and do not say: "We have seen the error of our ways," for you have not been blind: your faith has seen it, even though you did not see it. And the wind blows where it is. But after this I have not made it. I will set them aside. Their former glory is dust; and their latter glory, as the flowers of heaven, are like the foliage of a tree, Which like its shadow is no more.
